HEADWORD: Plicidentine
<hw>Plic`i*den"tine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>plica</ets> fold + E. <ets>dentine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>A form of dentine which shows sinuous lines of structure in a
transverse section of the tooth.</def>⟦br⟧
